				\begin{document}$$\left\{ {OD_{k} } \right\}_{k = 1}^{n}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M18"><mml:msubsup><mml:mfenced close="}" open="{"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>O</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mi>k</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mrow><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mi>n</mml:mi></mml:msubsup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2021_4064_Article_IEq6.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, where <italic>n</italic> is the number of pixels of the TRF scan; <italic>L</italic><sub><italic>i</italic></sub> is the fragment size of pixel <italic>i</italic> within the sequence <inline-formula id="IEq7"><alternatives><tex-math id="M19">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
